# Services, Security, and Performance Rules

- API integration must go through service classes and endpoint builders; do not embed API URLs in UI code.
- Do not log tokens, contracts, secrets, or raw sensitive payloads.
- Treat all `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` values as public; never put private secrets in browser-exposed env variables.
- Avoid `dangerouslySetInnerHTML`; if unavoidable, require explicit sanitization.
- Keep network calls cancellable/abort-safe in high-frequency UI flows.
- Avoid N+1 request patterns in hooks/components; batch or reuse data when possible.
- Prefer server/API pagination and filtering over large client-side loops for list-heavy screens.
- Avoid heavy synchronous transformations in render paths; move to memoized selectors or pre-processing.
- Reuse existing chart/table wrappers and shared utilities before creating expensive new abstractions.
- Keep `next.config.mjs` constraints in mind (`reactStrictMode: false`, `images.unoptimized: true`) when proposing perf changes.
